pr_review_comment_body:
@skorokithakis I think this PEP8 looks ok.
https://travis-ci.org/keleshev/schema/jobs/183802776
So please tell me a problem if it still exists. I want to fix it

I would suggest the following:

```python
    try:
        return datetime.datetime.strptime(time_val, "%Y%m%d%H%M%S.%f")
    except ValueError:
        return datetime.datetime.strptime(time_val, '%Y%m%d%H%M%S')
```

A couple things:

* We use camel case for javascript (i.e. $scope.newDataEndData, not $scope.new_data_end_date)
* It's only necessary to set a $scope property when you want to access it from an angular template (which it doesn't look like you want to here).
* This is pretty verbose :) How about something like this:

```js
function getDateRange(fromDateDelta, sampleSize) {
   var fromDateMs = Date.now() - (fromDateDelta * 1000);
   return {
      start: new Date(fromDateMs - sampleSize).toISOString().slice(0, -5),
      end: new Date(fromDateMs).toISOString().slice(0, -5)
  }
}

var baseDateRange = getDateRange($scope.selectedBaseDate, $scope.selectedSampleSize);
var newDateRange = getDateRange($scope.selectedNewDate, $scope.selectedSampleSize);
```

Extracted the repetitive code out.Changed code looks more cleaner.
```
    if ref_obj is not None and ucsgenutils.list_has_values(ref_obj):
        for mo in ref_obj:
            if filter_mo_to_compare(mo) is None:
                continue
            reference_dict[mo.dn] = mo

    if diff_obj is not None and ucsgenutils.list_has_values(diff_obj):
        for mo in diff_obj:
            if filter_mo_to_compare(mo) is None:
                continue
            translated_mo = _translate_managed_object(mo, xlate_org, xlate_map)
            difference_dict[translated_mo.dn] = translated_mo
```
